  "body": "Example: LibraryMake has this, a short para and indented code section.\n\n/Build.pm\n\n```\nuse Panda::Common;\nuse Panda::Builder;\nuse LibraryMake;\nuse Shell::Command;\n\nclass Build is Panda::Builder {\n    method build($workdir) {\n        my $makefiledir = \"$workdir/src\";\n        my $destdir = \"$workdir/blib/lib/My/Module\";\n        mkpath $destdir;\n        make($makefiledir, $destdir);\n    }\n}\n```\n\np6doc renders it thusly:\n\n/Build.pm\n\n```\nuse Panda::Common; use Panda::Builder; use LibraryMake; use Shell::Command;\n\nclass Build is Panda::Builder {\n    method build($workdir) {\n        my $makefiledir = \"$workdir/src\"; my $destdir =\n        \"$workdir/blib/lib/My/Module\"; mkpath $destdir; make($makefiledir,\n        $destdir);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nperl6 --doc /path/to/Librarymake.pm6 renders correctly:\n\n/Build.pm\n\n```\nuse Panda::Common;\nuse Panda::Builder;\nuse LibraryMake;\nuse Shell::Command;\n\nclass Build is Panda::Builder {\n    method build($workdir) {\n        my $makefiledir = \"$workdir/src\";\n        my $destdir = \"$workdir/blib/lib/My/Module\";\n        mkpath $destdir;\n        make($makefiledir, $destdir);\n    }\n}\n```\n",
